# Arbitrage Scanner Frontend (Next.js)
## Getting Started
1. Clone the repository to your local machine:
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/vivekbopaliya/arbitrage-scanner.git
    ```
2. Install dependencies:
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```
3. Start the development server:
    ```bash
    npm run dev
    ```
4. To start hitting the backend (ws://localhost:3001), you will need to start our Node.js backend. For that, check this [repository](https://github.com/vivekbopaliya/arbitrage-scanner-ws)

And you are good to go!
